00:05:56.389 --> 00:06:00.660 line:95%,end
Because my mother died of cancer.
My mom died of a really awful--

00:06:00.793 --> 00:06:03.096 line:95%,end
I mean, she died in nine months.
And it was awful.

00:06:03.429 --> 00:06:04.530 line:95%,end
ABBY: It is.

00:06:04.597 --> 00:06:08.534 line:5%,start
My mom, she had cancer,
and it was an awful cancer.

00:06:08.601 --> 00:06:14.974 line:95%,end
She went really fast.
Um, cancer just sucks.

00:06:15.641 --> 00:06:18.411 line:95%,end
And I think that we're all
affected by it in some way.

00:06:18.511 --> 00:06:22.682 line:95%,end
People are living with cancer.
Children are living with cancer.

00:06:22.749 --> 00:06:24.250 line:95%,end
They're surviving.

00:06:24.317 --> 00:06:26.819 line:95%,end
Both of my grandfathers died from cancer,

00:06:26.919 --> 00:06:30.056 line:95%,end
and my dad actually has cancer right now.
He has prostate cancer.

00:06:30.256 --> 00:06:33.459 line:95%,end
So doing the dance Living with the Ribbon
really means a lot to me.

00:06:33.793 --> 00:06:36.295 line:95%,end
ABBY: This is a piece
that I've wanted to do.

00:06:36.396 --> 00:06:39.899 line:95%,end
