or sorry, I said that?

00:11:27.553 --> 00:11:29.455 line:95%,end
No, you know, I'm, I'm just kind of,

00:11:29.522 --> 00:11:32.591 line:95%,end
like, I'm just kind of
taking a break right now.

00:11:33.592 --> 00:11:36.095 line:95%,end
I left it in her corner
and I'm leaving it in her corner.

00:11:36.362 --> 00:11:38.764 line:95%,end
I'm not begging someone like,
please like me, please like me.

00:11:38.831 --> 00:11:41.233 line:95%,end
I thought our friendship
was worth more than that.

00:11:41.667 --> 00:11:43.803 line:95%,end
It is, which says--
CHRISTI: You feel that way.

00:11:44.303 --> 00:11:47.106 line:95%,end
I feel that way.
Clearly, Kelly doesn't feel that way.

00:11:47.173 --> 00:11:50.743 line:95%,end
And I don't want to be like that.

00:11:51.110 --> 00:11:55.548 line:95%,end
And right then, I said to myself,
she's not a best friend.


00:12:02.888 --> 00:12:04.623 line:95%,end
MADDIE: Chloe, play yours.

00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:09.595 line:95%,end
- It's the same.
- It is the same.

00:12:10.362 --> 00:12:13.165 line:5%,start
We're in the den, and Maddie
decides to play her solo music,

00:12:13.232 --> 00:12:16.769 line:5%,start
and I'm like, whoa,
that's Chloe's solo music.

00:12:16.836 --> 00:12:19.772 line:95%,end
So then it finally hits me that
Abby is giving the two of them

00:12:20.005 --> 00:12:21.607 line:95%,end
the exact same solo.

00:12:24.744 --> 00:12:26.278 line:95%,end
Why do I the same--

00:12:26.378 --> 00:12:28.547 line:95%,end
- Why do we have the same dance?
MELISSA: It's fine.

00:12:30.950 --> 00:12:33.586 line:5%,start
I was just so confused,
because I'm not used

00:12:33.686 --> 00:12:35.654 line:95%,end
to doing the same exact dance.

00:12:35.721 --> 00:12:38.657 line:95%,end
Wait, why do we have the same
song but it's different names?

00:12:39.825 --> 00:12:41.560 line:95%,end
So that we wouldn't catch on.

00:12:41.660 --> 00:12:45.464 line:95%,end
This week, I think Abby decided to
teach me a lesson more than anyone.

00:12:45.531 --> 00:12:48.134 line:95%,end
So Chloe and Maddie are
given the exact same music,

00:12:48.234 --> 00:12:51.003 line:95%,end
the exact same choreography,
the exact same costume,

00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:53.205 line:95%,end
because I always say,
let's even the playing field

00:12:53.272 --> 00:12:54.774 line:95%,end
and see where the chips fall.

00:12:55.207 --> 00:12:58.043 line:95%,end
MADDIE: So, like,
same choreography, same song,

00:12:58.144 --> 00:12:59.979 line:95%,end
same costumes, same dance.

00:13:00.579 --> 00:13:03.949 line:95%,end
KELLY: Did we learn on the same day?
MADDIE: Yeah. Yes, we did.

00:13:04.016 --> 00:13:05.384 line:95%,end
KELLY: OK.

00:13:09.722 --> 00:13:12.792 line:5%,start
JILL: You guys totally sure
you have the exact same number?

00:13:12.958 --> 00:13:13.959 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Yeah.

00:13:14.026 --> 00:13:16.595 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Well, it depends
on who choreographed it for,

00:13:17.863 --> 00:13:19.665 line:95%,end
because they have different strengths.

00:13:19.999 --> 00:13:23.002 line:95%,end
I'm always complaining that Chloe has
lesser choreography than Maddie.

00:13:23.068 --> 00:13:25.938 line:95%,end
So Abby's saying, you know what,
here, do Maddie's choreography.

00:13:26.005 --> 00:13:29.074 line:95%,end
And I think that she made sure
that it was Maddie's dance.

00:13:29.141 --> 00:13:32.011 line:95%,end
KRISTIE RAY: So is Maddie concerned
with having the same routine?

00:13:32.511 --> 00:13:34.413 line:95%,end
MELISSA: No, I think she's confused.

00:13:34.713 --> 00:13:36.715 line:95%,end
I don't think she's concerned,
not at all, no.

00:13:36.782 --> 00:13:38.651 line:95%,end
Like, it's never happened before.

00:13:39.251 --> 00:13:42.955 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Hm, you know
never say never at the ALDC.

00:13:43.055 --> 00:13:45.391 line:95%,end
HOLLY: I think she's just saying
that better dancer's going to win.

00:13:45.491 --> 00:13:47.560 line:95%,end
Because you could strip
all this other stuff away,

00:13:47.626 --> 00:13:51.931 line:95%,end
when it comes down to what, it's going
to be X, whatever X factor happens.

00:13:52.364 --> 00:13:58.037 line:95%,end
It makes a very uncomfortable situation
for both girls and for all of us.

00:13:58.137 --> 00:14:00.906 line:95%,end
I mean, just going into
the Green room afterwards,

00:14:00.973 --> 00:14:02.842 line:95%,end
one of them is going to win,
and one of them isn't.

00:14:02.908 --> 00:14:05.411 line:95%,end
- This is Chloe's chance to show Abby.
- Exactly.

00:14:05.544 --> 00:14:07.613 line:95%,end
You know what, you say
Maddie's the best every week.

00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:09.548 line:95%,end
Well, when you give them
the same amount of time,

00:14:09.615 --> 00:14:11.450 line:95%,end
and the same choreography,
and the same dance,

00:14:11.517 --> 00:14:13.118 line:95%,end
look what can happen.

00:14:13.185 --> 00:14:16.121 line:5%,start
I don't like
how Abby has Chloe and Maddie

00:14:16.222 --> 00:14:17.756 line:95%,end
doing the same solos this week.

00:14:17.857 --> 00:14:20.192 line:95%,end
I just feel like no matter what happens,

00:14:20.593 --> 00:14:24.396 line:95%,end
one of the kids is going to be upset.
And I don't think that's fair.

00:14:24.496 --> 00:14:27.867 line:95%,end
This is as equal of a level playing field
you're ever going to get.

00:14:29.001 --> 00:14:31.203 line:5%,start
[MUSIC - TUMBLEDOWN
HOUSE, "OLD POTOSI"]

00:14:36.775 --> 00:14:39.078 line:5%,start
I want Asia and Mackenzie
to watch one another

00:14:39.144 --> 00:14:42.514 line:5%,start
during rehearsal, so they can
see what they're up against.

00:14:49.989 --> 00:14:52.057 line:95%,end
All right.
Asia, you're up.


00:14:54.093 --> 00:14:56.295 line:95%,end
- Hey!
KRISTIE RAY: Come over?

00:14:56.462 --> 00:14:57.463 line:95%,end
Oh, shoes.

00:14:57.563 --> 00:14:59.632 line:95%,end
Can you-- shoes, and
then come on over here.

00:14:59.698 --> 00:15:04.270 line:95%,end
JILL: Kristie Ray gets to go down
and watch Asia do her solo.

00:15:04.336 --> 00:15:06.639 line:5%,start
We don't get to do that with our kids.

00:15:06.705 --> 00:15:08.207 line:5%,start
It's just not fair.

00:15:08.941 --> 00:15:11.911 line:5%,start
[MUSIC - TRIFECTA, "2 HOT 2 HANDLE"]

00:15:15.247 --> 00:15:18.450 line:95%,end
TRIFECTA: (SINGING) Oh, here it comes.
Here it comes.

00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:20.486 line:95%,end
It's always the same.

00:15:20.552 --> 00:15:21.954 line:95%,end
Can we go--

00:15:22.021 --> 00:15:25.090 line:95%,end
I hope you get to sit in there
and watch your kid and get--

00:15:25.224 --> 00:15:26.692 line:95%,end
- I don't get in--
JILL: --get all that.

00:15:26.759 --> 00:15:30.062 line:95%,end
Yeah, but you know what, you should.
She's competing head to head with Asia.

00:15:30.129 --> 00:15:31.330 line:95%,end
I don't wanna sit back--

00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:33.032 line:95%,end
JILL: You should get the
same treatment she's getting.

00:15:33.132 --> 00:15:34.800 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Nope, I'm fine with
just the treatment I'm getting.

00:15:34.900 --> 00:15:37.236 line:95%,end
I don't need to be in there.
I like to look at it up here.

00:15:43.075 --> 00:15:44.777 line:5%,start
JILL: I think we are incognito.

00:15:44.877 --> 00:15:46.412 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: We're in black with sunglasses.

00:15:46.545 --> 00:15:48.047 line:95%,end
No one will ever know.

00:15:48.447 --> 00:15:50.549 line:95%,end
Both Melissa's kids are
doing solos this week.

00:15:50.716 --> 00:15:52.584 line:95%,end
And Maddie is going
head to head with Chloe.

00:15:52.685 --> 00:15:56.255 line:95%,end
Of course, Melissa's going to do
everything that she can

00:15:56.355 --> 00:15:58.190 line:95%,end
to give Maddie the edge this week.

00:15:58.357 --> 00:16:01.327 line:95%,end
Melissa will lose her [bleep]
if both of her kids lose.

00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:05.197 line:95%,end
JILL: Our plan is to prove what we have
known all along,

00:16:05.798 --> 00:16:08.934 line:95%,end
that Maddie gets extra private time.

00:16:09.001 --> 00:16:11.603 line:95%,end
We know what's going on.
We need proof.

00:16:11.670 --> 00:16:14.606 line:95%,end
We have to videotape it,
because Melissa always says,

00:16:14.807 --> 00:16:17.109 line:95%,end
oh, my kids didn't learn it.
And every week, we see it.

00:16:17.176 --> 00:16:18.444 line:95%,end
But we never have evidence.

00:16:18.510 --> 00:16:22.514 line:95%,end
I am so sick of Melissa sitting upstairs
and lying to us every week.

00:16:22.781 --> 00:16:24.616 line:95%,end
Oh, my kids didn't learn their solos.

00:16:24.750 --> 00:16:27.753 line:95%,end
They just happened to know
by osmosis which move comes next.

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:29.788 line:95%,end
No, they happen to know
which move comes next

00:16:29.855 --> 00:16:31.323 line:95%,end
because they already learned their dance.

00:16:31.390 --> 00:16:32.791 line:95%,end
- All right.
- We know what's going on.

00:16:32.891 --> 00:16:34.259 line:5%,start
All right.
Let's do it.

00:16:35.561 --> 00:16:37.696 line:5%,start
How do you think those kids go in there
know everything?

00:16:37.830 --> 00:16:39.898 line:95%,end
It's not because
they're, like, just super geniuses.

00:16:39.999 --> 00:16:41.333 line:95%,end
They grub it.

00:16:41.867 --> 00:16:44.837 line:95%,end
Wait, look.
Gia and Janine's cars are here.

00:16:44.970 --> 00:16:47.840 line:95%,end
Janine always choreographs
Mackenzie, and--

00:16:48.007 --> 00:16:49.742 line:95%,end
BOTH: Gia does Maddie.

00:16:49.908 --> 00:16:51.477 line:95%,end
[gasps] They're both--

00:16:51.577 --> 00:16:53.112 line:95%,end
They're both learning their dances.

00:16:53.245 --> 00:16:55.581 line:95%,end
I knew that Maddie
and Mackenzie were inside

00:16:55.681 --> 00:16:58.450 line:95%,end
getting extra rehearsal time,
extra privates,

00:16:58.550 --> 00:17:01.620 line:95%,end
and you know what,
Melissa just doesn't play fair.

00:17:01.887 --> 00:17:04.556 line:95%,end
Well, what am I recording?
Just the sound or do you want me to--

00:17:04.656 --> 00:17:06.458 line:95%,end
No, I want you to get in that studio.

00:17:06.592 --> 00:17:08.327 line:95%,end
I'll stand watch.

00:17:09.962 --> 00:17:11.497 line:95%,end
Jill likes to get to the bottom of things.

00:17:11.563 --> 00:17:13.465 line:95%,end
She likes to know
everything that's going on.

00:17:13.532 --> 00:17:16.835 line:95%,end
So clearly, if there's a secret,
Jill's the one who's going to unearth it.

00:17:21.340 --> 00:17:22.341 line:95%,end
[bleep]

00:17:22.441 --> 00:17:23.909 line:95%,end
My glasses!

00:17:24.643 --> 00:17:26.378 line:95%,end
[inaudible chatter]

00:17:28.547 --> 00:17:30.115 line:95%,end
Oh, they're in my pocket.

00:17:30.282 --> 00:17:32.851 line:95%,end
She has a partner in crime, like Kelly,
I have you.

00:17:34.653 --> 00:17:36.355 line:95%,end
- Did you get video?
- I got video.

00:17:36.822 --> 00:17:38.223 line:95%,end
- Who?
- Maddie.

00:17:38.357 --> 00:17:39.591 line:95%,end
Oh.


00:17:42.227 --> 00:17:45.664 line:5%,start
ABBY: All right. So you obviously figured
out that you're doing the same routine.

00:17:47.566 --> 00:17:50.969 line:95%,end
When you go to an audition,
aren't you all given the same combination?

00:17:51.303 --> 00:17:56.041 line:95%,end
Yes. And that's really the main reason
why I did this exercise.

00:17:56.108 --> 00:18:00.279 line:5%,start
This week, I'm giving Maddie
and Chloe the exact same solo.

00:18:00.913 --> 00:18:05.250 line:95%,end
This is going to prepare them for a career
in the professional dance world.

00:18:05.551 --> 00:18:10.989 line:95%,end
Sometimes, when you win, I hear
a whole bunch from your mommy.

00:18:11.356 --> 00:18:14.593 line:95%,end
And what I hear is,
well, if Chloe would have

00:18:14.660 --> 00:18:17.529 line:95%,end
Maddie's choreography,
if they would pay that much attention

00:18:17.596 --> 00:18:20.866 line:95%,end
to my Chloe, if this, if that--
It's one excuse after another.

00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:24.636 line:95%,end
And some of them are
pretty darn offensive to me.

00:18:24.703 --> 00:18:26.338 line:95%,end
It's do or die time.

00:18:26.672 --> 00:18:31.677 line:95%,end
Christi, it's time for you
to put up and shut up.

00:18:31.743 --> 00:18:34.713 line:95%,end
Chloe, turn around.
Turn to the front of the door.

00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:36.448 line:95%,end
She's not letting them watch each other.

00:18:36.748 --> 00:18:38.650 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: It's like
the Blair Witch Project.

00:18:39.151 --> 00:18:41.687 line:5%,start
ABBY: Let the body and the head go
with that straddle leap.

00:18:42.621 --> 00:18:44.123 line:95%,end
MELISSA: What's the purpose?

00:18:44.590 --> 00:18:46.492 line:95%,end
You know, if she wants them
to be motivated,

00:18:46.592 --> 00:18:48.994 line:95%,end
they need to watch each other
and motivate one another.

00:18:49.061 --> 00:18:51.396 line:95%,end
ABBY: Finish the movement for the arms.

00:18:52.998 --> 00:18:54.133 line:95%,end
All right.

00:18:54.233 --> 00:18:56.835 line:95%,end
[music - "you can be anything"]

00:18:58.303 --> 00:19:03.442 line:95%,end
It takes a moment to break a butterfly.
On the way--

00:19:03.542 --> 00:19:04.843 line:95%,end
- Which is weird.
- I know.

00:19:04.943 --> 00:19:06.078 line:95%,end
- I'm sorry.
- Face the wall.

00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:08.447 line:95%,end
HOLLY: You see them both working
on a solo at the same time.

00:19:08.514 --> 00:19:10.582 line:95%,end
The judges be like,
didn't I just see this dance?

00:19:11.116 --> 00:19:13.619 line:95%,end
[music - "you can be anything"]
I still hear them say,

00:19:14.953 --> 00:19:21.093 line:95%,end
You can be anything, anything,

00:19:21.160 --> 00:19:23.395 line:95%,end
anything you dreamed of.

00:19:23.495 --> 00:19:27.599 line:95%,end
This is a toss-up, and I think
both of them want this bad.

00:19:27.799 --> 00:19:29.501 line:95%,end
They're both dancing great.

00:19:29.601 --> 00:19:30.836 line:95%,end
Good, good.

00:19:30.903 --> 00:19:33.238 line:95%,end
Is the reason why you're so quiet
is because

00:19:33.305 --> 00:19:36.308 line:95%,end
you don't have any complaints
or is it because you're satisfied?

00:19:36.375 --> 00:19:37.676 line:95%,end
I have some other things going on.

00:19:37.743 --> 00:19:39.111 line:95%,end
KRISTIE RAY: I think you're
preoccupied in your mind.

00:19:39.178 --> 00:19:40.479 line:5%,start
OK, OK.

00:19:40.546 --> 00:19:44.283 line:5%,start
I really do have a lot on my mind,
and she's sitting right to the left of me.

00:19:44.883 --> 00:19:46.451 line:95%,end
ABBY: You're dismissed.
Thank you very much.

00:19:46.618 --> 00:19:49.388 line:95%,end
Grab a drink and bring the group in.
OK, girls!

00:19:49.655 --> 00:19:51.323 line:95%,end
Well, where's the pink ribbon?

00:19:51.957 --> 00:19:53.392 line:95%,end
I need that, like, right now.

00:19:53.825 --> 00:19:55.861 line:95%,end
Now, you would think the moms
would want to help out

00:19:55.961 --> 00:19:59.097 line:95%,end
and get the ribbon to the kids.
But no, it's still not ready.

00:19:59.431 --> 00:20:03.135 line:95%,end
I have a little job
for my two favorite Dance Moms.

00:20:03.202 --> 00:20:05.537 line:95%,end
So you want me to go ask them
to find the white elastic,

00:20:05.637 --> 00:20:08.140 line:95%,end
find the light pink dye, and dye it?

00:20:08.207 --> 00:20:10.809 line:95%,end
Give it to Christi and Kelly.

00:20:11.276 --> 00:20:12.644 line:95%,end
All right.

00:20:13.245 --> 00:20:14.513 line:95%,end
I have a request.

00:20:14.746 --> 00:20:16.148 line:95%,end
No, it's not from me, from Maddie.

00:20:16.315 --> 00:20:19.851 line:95%,end
She wants Miss Christi
and Kelly to go downstairs.

00:20:19.918 --> 00:20:22.588 line:95%,end
- All right. Let's go.
- Do we need instructions?

00:20:23.322 --> 00:20:24.556 line:95%,end
I think we could figure it out.


00:20:24.656 --> 00:20:26.692 line:5%,start
MELISSA: Christi and Kelly
in the same room together?

00:20:27.025 --> 00:20:28.660 line:5%,start
I don't know how this
is going to turn out.

00:20:28.727 --> 00:20:30.929 line:95%,end
I think it's great that
Christi and Kelly were picked

00:20:31.029 --> 00:20:34.166 line:95%,end
to go down because I think
maybe that will kind of break the ice.

00:20:34.833 --> 00:20:37.102 line:95%,end
[suspenseful music]

00:20:43.242 --> 00:20:45.944 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Well, hopefully,
they are using this time

00:20:46.011 --> 00:20:50.716 line:95%,end
to just talk, or laugh, or let go,
and it's not so intense.

00:20:50.782 --> 00:20:52.884 line:95%,end
I think it's, what, been a week.

00:20:53.151 --> 00:20:55.554 line:95%,end
I think they want it to go away.
I really do.

00:20:55.621 --> 00:20:57.656 line:95%,end
- I don't.
- I don't think they'll ever be the same.

00:21:05.864 --> 00:21:07.966 line:95%,end
ABBY: Hey, moms!
You want to come on down here?

00:21:08.033 --> 00:21:11.536 line:95%,end
I have the costumes, and I want to talk
about the routine a little bit!

00:21:11.603 --> 00:21:13.572 line:95%,end
What's going to go down this weekend.
Come on.

00:21:16.708 --> 00:21:18.543 line:95%,end
KELLY: Oh, they're very sheer.

00:21:18.610 --> 00:21:20.145 line:95%,end
ABBY: Listen to me.

00:21:20.245 --> 00:21:23.915 line:95%,end
How many people here know
somebody that's died of cancer?

00:21:29.454 --> 00:21:31.490 line:95%,end
Is that a painful thing?

00:21:31.556 --> 00:21:34.493 line:95%,end
Is it a loss of dignity?

00:21:34.559 --> 00:21:36.028 line:95%,end
You know what that means, girls?

00:21:36.128 --> 00:21:38.563 line:95%,end
You're not in control of your body.

00:21:39.264 --> 00:21:42.501 line:95%,end
Yes, you feel this big.

00:21:45.604 --> 00:21:48.040 line:95%,end
How many of you think
you can live through that?

00:21:54.246 --> 00:21:55.981 line:95%,end
I did that.

00:21:59.318 --> 00:22:01.320 line:95%,end
I had to do that.

00:22:01.887 --> 00:22:03.789 line:95%,end
My dad had a brain tumor.

00:22:04.523 --> 00:22:07.125 line:95%,end
He had a seizure and collapsed
on the bathroom floor.

00:22:08.627 --> 00:22:11.096 line:95%,end
It's not pretty.

00:22:11.797 --> 00:22:14.399 line:95%,end
And you're all very pretty.

00:22:16.068 --> 00:22:17.636 line:95%,end
Come here.

00:22:18.570 --> 00:22:22.341 line:95%,end
Right now,
people are living with the ribbon.

00:22:22.407 --> 00:22:24.776 line:95%,end
People are living with cancer every day.

00:22:25.811 --> 00:22:28.380 line:95%,end
And that's what you're showing.
That's what the dance is about.

00:22:29.548 --> 00:22:30.982 line:95%,end
Are you crying because I'm sad?

00:22:31.583 --> 00:22:33.385 line:95%,end
Who, who passed away?

00:22:33.885 --> 00:22:35.887 line:95%,end
Well, my dad when I wasn't born--

00:22:35.954 --> 00:22:38.123 line:95%,end
but it was, like, a long time ago.

00:22:38.290 --> 00:22:40.759 line:95%,end
My dad, his dog, Diablo died.

00:22:41.193 --> 00:22:42.994 line:95%,end
It was just so hard for him.

00:22:44.162 --> 00:22:46.565 line:95%,end
ABBY: His what?
His daughter?

00:22:47.165 --> 00:22:48.266 line:95%,end
No, his dog.

00:22:48.333 --> 00:22:49.668 line:5%,start
